<DocLayout title="Team & Leadership" description="The people behind the AEGIS Initiative — human-directed governance for autonomous AI.">
  <h1>Team &amp; Leadership</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>Founder &amp; Principal</h2>
    <p>
      The AEGIS Initiative was founded and is led by <strong>Kenneth Tannenbaum</strong>.
      Ken serves as the organization's sole principal, chief architect, and
      decision-making authority. All governance decisions, architectural choices,
      policy positions, and publications are directed by Ken.
    </p>
    <p>
      Ken brings experience in software engineering, systems architecture, and
      security to the challenge of AI governance. The AEGIS Initiative was founded
      on the premise that the governance problem in AI is not a research gap — it
      is an engineering gap. The frameworks exist in principle; AEGIS makes them
      enforceable in practice.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>AI Collaboration</h2>
    <p>
      The AEGIS Initiative is <strong>human-directed and AI-collaborated</strong>.
      AI tools are used openly and deliberately as productivity instruments:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Claude Code</strong> — primary development and research partner</li>
      <li><strong>Claude.ai</strong> — drafting, analysis, and editorial review</li>
      <li><strong>ChatGPT</strong> — research and cross-referencing</li>
      <li><strong>DALL-E &amp; MidJourney</strong> — visual assets and branding</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Every document, specification, and publication is reviewed, approved, and
      published by a human. AI-generated content is always subject to human
      editorial judgment. We believe this transparency strengthens — rather than
      weakens — the credibility of governance work.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Growing the Team</h2>
    <p>
      As the initiative grows, we intend to expand the team with domain experts
      in AI safety, public policy, legal frameworks, and systems engineering.
      We are also exploring the formation of an advisory board composed of
      practitioners and researchers in AI governance.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you're interested in contributing to the AEGIS Initiative — whether as
      a collaborator, advisor, or sponsor — please <a href="/contact/">get in touch</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocLayout>
